---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead title="About — 0xmiikey" description="Co-founder & CTO at UQPAY. Builder at the intersection of fintech, AI, and global payment infrastructure." />
</head>
<body>
  <Header />
  <main style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem 2rem;">

    <h1 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--fg);">About</h1>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 3rem;">MIIKEY · Co-founder & CTO · Payment Infrastructure</p>

    <div class="prose">

      <p>
        I'm an engineer who went deep enough into product to become a founder.
        Co-founded <a href="https://uqpay.com" target="_blank">UQPAY</a> — a global payment
        infrastructure company focused on making cross-border transactions faster, cheaper, and more
        reliable. As CTO, I own the full engineering stack: architecture decisions, team building,
        and the harder problem of keeping a technical team effective as the ground shifts under us.
      </p>

      <img
        src="/images/about-builder.jpg"
        alt="Building at the intersection of fintech, crypto, and AI"
        style="width:100%; height:320px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border); margin:2rem 0;"
      />

      <p>
        Before UQPAY, I spent years in DeFi — contributing to protocol frontends, building analytics
        tooling, and getting very familiar with what it actually takes to ship products in adversarial,
        high-stakes environments. The crypto ecosystem taught me to build defensively, move
        deliberately, and treat every design decision as a tradeoff.
      </p>

      <h2>What I think about</h2>

      <p>
        The thing I keep coming back to: <strong>AI is not just a productivity tool — it's a
        reorganization of how product development works.</strong> The boundary between "product" and
        "engineering" is collapsing. The question of what a 10-person team can build is being
        renegotiated in real time.
      </p>

      <img
        src="/images/about-ai.jpg"
        alt="AI reshaping how engineering and product teams operate"
        style="width:100%; height:280px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border); margin:1.5rem 0;"
      />

      <p>
        For people running technical teams, this creates a specific kind of discomfort. The mental
        models we used to evaluate engineers, structure roadmaps, and decide what to build — those
        models are all up for revision. I write about this because I'm living it, not because I have
        clean answers.
      </p>

      <h2>On payments and crypto</h2>

      <p>
        Payments is a sector that looks solved from the outside and is completely unsolved from the
        inside. The moment you cross a border — whether geographic, regulatory, or currency — the
        friction becomes brutal. UQPAY is my attempt to fix that with infrastructure that doesn't
        apologize for complexity.
      </p>

      <img
        src="/images/about-payments.jpg"
        alt="Cross-border payments — the infrastructure problem that looks solved but isn't"
        style="width:100%; height:280px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:8px; border:1px solid var(--border); margin:1.5rem 0;"
      />

      <p>
        I believe crypto-native payment rails will matter. Not as a speculative bet, but as an
        engineering argument: programmable money is strictly more capable than legacy payment systems.
        The adoption curve is a UX and trust problem, not a technology problem.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>

      <p>
        The best way to reach me is <a href="https://twitter.com/0xmiikey" target="_blank">@0xmiikey</a>
        on X. I respond to thoughtful DMs. Also on <a href="https://github.com/miikey" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
        if you want to look at code.
      </p>

    </div>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>
